An administrative region of Ghana. Located in mid-western Ghana, between the Ashanti Region and the Cote d'Ivoire border. Its capital is Sunyani.

An administrative region of Ghana. It is bordered by the Ashanti and Eastern regions to the north, Western region to the west, Greater Accra region to the east, and to the south by the Atlantic Ocean.
An administrative region of Ghana.
An administrative region of Ghana.

An administrative region of Ghana. The region lies in the north of the country and is bordered in the northwest by the Upper West Region, in the northeast by the Upper East Region, in the southwest by the Brong-Ahafo Region, in the southeast by the Volta Region, in the west by Cote d'Ivoire (the Ivory Coast) and in the east by Togo.
An administrative region of Ghana. It is located in the northeastern corner of the country and bordered by Burkina Faso to the north and Togo to the east. The capital is Bolgatanga.
An administrative region of Ghana. It is located in the northwestern corner of the country and is bordered by Burkina Faso to the north. The capital and largest city is Wa.
An administrative region of Ghana. It is located to the east of Lake Volta. Its capital is Ho.
An administrative region of Ghana.
An administrative region in central Ghana.
An administrative region of Guinea.
An administrative refion of Guinea. Located in east-central Guinea. It is bordered by the countries of Sierra Leone and Mali and the Guinean regions of Kankan, Mamou, Nzerekore, and Labe.
An administrative region of Guinea. Located in eastern Guinea. It is bordered by the countries of Mali and Cote d'Ivoire and the Guinean regions of Nzerekore and Faranah.
An administrative region of Guinea. Located in western Guinea. It is bordered by the country of Sierra Leone and the Guinean regions of Conakry, Labe, Mamou, and Boke.
An administrative region of Guinea. Located in north-central Guinea. It is bordered by the countries of Senegal and Mali and the Guinean regions of Faranah, Kindia, Mamou, and Boke.
An administrative region of Guinea. Located in central Guinea. It is bordered by the country of Sierra Leone and the Guinean regions of Faranah, Labe, and Kindia.
An administrative region of Guinea. It is bordered by the countries of Sierra Leone, Liberia, and Cote d'Ivoire and the Guinean regions of Kankan and Faranah.

An administrative region of Guinea. It is located in western Guinea. It is bordered by the countries of Senegal and Guinea-Bissau and the Guinean regions of Kindia and Labe. Its capital is the city of Boke.

A county in the northernmost part of Liberia. It is bordered by Bong County to the south and Gbarpolu County to the west. The northwestern parts of Lofa border the nation of Sierra Leone and the northeaster parts border Guinea.

A county in tne NW of Liberia. It is bordered by Grand Cape Mount County to the west, Bomi County to the southwest, Bong County to the south, and Lofa County to the east and north. The northwest part of Gbarpolu borders the nation of Sierra Leone.

A county in the NW part of Liberia. It is bordered by Gbarpolu County to the northeast and Bomi County to the southeast. The northern part of Grand Cape Mount borders the nation of Sierra Leone, while to the west lies the Atlantic Ocean.

A county on the north to central coast of Liberia. It is bordered by Montserrado County to the west, Grand Bassa County to the east, and Bong County on the north. The southern part of Margibi lies on the Atlantic Ocean.

A county in the west-central part of Liberia. It is bordered by Margibi County to the northwest, Bong County to the north, Nimba County to the east, and River Cess County to the south and east. The western part of Grand Bassa borders the Atlantic Ocean.

A county in the southeastern part of Liberia. The county is bordered by Grand Kru County to the west and River Gee County to the north. The eastern part of Maryland borders the nation of Cote d'Ivoire, separated by the Cavalla River.

A county in the southeastern part of Liberia. It is bordered by River Gee County to the northeast, Sinoe County to the northwest, and Maryland County to the southeast. The southern part of Grand Kru borders the Atlantic Ocean.

A county in the eastern part of Liberia. It is bordered by Nimba County to the west, Sinoe County to the southwest, and River Gee County to the southeast. The northern part of Grand Gedeh borders the nation of Cote d'Ivoire.

A district in the north-central part of Liberia. It is bordered by Lofa and Gbarpolu counties to the north, Margibi and Montserrado counties to the west, Grand Bassa County to the south, and Nimba County to the east. The northeast part of Bong borders the nation of Guinea.

A county in the south-central part of Liberia. It is bordered by Grand Bassa County to the west, Nimba County on the northeast, and Sinoe County to the southeast. The southern part of River Cess lies on the Atlantic Ocean.

A county in the north-central portion of the West African nation of Liberia. Nimba is bordered by Bong and Grand Bassa counties to the west, River Cess County to the southwest, and Grand Gedeh County to the southeast. The northern and northeastern parts of Nimba borders the nation of Guinea, while the northeast lies along the border of Cote d'Ivoire.

A county in the southern part of Liberia. It is bordered by Sinoe County to the west, Grand Gedeh County to the north, and Grand Kru and Maryland counties to the south. The eastern part of River Gee borders the nation of Ivory Coast along the Cavalla River.
A county of Liberia.

A county in the northwestern portion of the West African nation of Liberia. The county is bordered by Bomi County to the west, Bong County to the north, and Margibi County to the east. The southern part of Montserrado lies on the Atlantic Coast.

A part of Nigeria. The Territory was formed in 1976 from parts of former Nasarawa, Niger, and Kogi States. The territory is located just north of the confluence of the Niger and Benue rivers. It is bordered by the states of Niger to the West and North, Kaduna to the northeast, Nasarawa to the east and south, and Kogi to the southwest.

A state in northeastern Nigeria, with its capital at Yola. It is bordered by the states of Borno to the northwest, Gombe to the west and Taraba to the southwest. Its eastern border also forms the national eastern border with Cameroon.

A state in Nigeria. It is located in the coastal south-Southern part of the country. It is bordered on the east by Cross River State, on the west by Rivers State and Abia State, and on the South by the Atlantic Ocean and Cross River State again. Akwa Ibom State was created out of Cross River State on 1987-09-23.
